The paper discusses a machine learning problem of learning how to order instances based on preference judgments. This falls under the category of learning to rank, which is a subfield of machine learning and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and strategies, which are common in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the problem of finding the best ordering, which is a computational complexity problem (cs.CC).
